        Generate a vector of x elements where the nth element contains a vector of the prime factors of n.

        Input:
        x, a constrained integer greater than 1

        Output:
        E, a vector of x elements where the nth element contains a vector of the prime factors of n

        Parameters:
        x - the upper limit of the search for primes
        Returns:
        an array of List<Integer> where each List contains the prime factors of the index of the List; elements 0 and 1 are null

      • product

        static int product(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> X)
        Product of the integers in a vector.

        Modified form of the function for use within the search for prime factors. The restriction to integer range is appropriate because we never factor numbers outside this range.

        Inputs:
        X, a vector of positive integers of arbitrary length

        Outputs:
        y, an unconstrained integer

        Parameters:
        X - a vector of positive integers of arbitrary length
        Returns:
        an integer
